<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Washburn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Jackson</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Portland,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-11"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 11, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Cargo of Chesapeake was owned entirely by American and Canadian
                                merchants, and was not intended to run blockade. Advise authorities
                                of fact, as the piracy was projected in St. John. I suppose they
                                will not permit Chesapeake to leave their ports.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>ISRAEL WASHBURN, <hi rend="smallcaps">Jr.,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Collector.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>